projects: [{'title': 'A zircon provenance study of the Kanye Basin (Botswana) to constrain terrestrial geodynamics across the Archaean-Proterozoic transition.', 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}, 'end': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}}, 'description': 'This study investigates, for the first time, the Neoarchaean to Paleoproterozoic Transvaal Supergroup sedimentary sequence in Botswana that formed in the centre of the Kaapvaal Craton during oxygenation of the atmosphere. We use combined Lu-Hf isotope and U-Pb dating on (sedimentary) zircons from throughout the sedimentary sequence to determine the tectono-magmatic evolution of the hinterland basement. This approach will constrain regional crustal growth, uplift and erosion events and establish if additional cratons were in the hinterland, e.g. Pilbara. The approach will provide an integrated assessment of Neoarchaean tectonics by considering erosion and crustal growth-reworking. Knowledge of provenance changes with time will aid in making tectonic reconstructions and allow critical comparison to\nknown tectonic scenarios, e.g. Alpine style molasse basin. The geochronology results will also provide an important contribution to improving stratigraphic correlations in the Transvaal Supergroup across the entire craton to help evaluate spatial and temporal variations in depositional environments associated with oxygenation of the atmosphere.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Denice', 'last_name': 'Borsten', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Master student geology and geochemistry'}]}, {'title': 'The geodynamical development of the Kaapvaal craton (Botswana); a zircon study based on the Black reef formation; Transvaal Supergroup and the Gaborone granite.', 'date': {'start': {'month': 5, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}, 'end': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2023}}, 'description': 'Master research project with fieldwork in Botswana planned in the upcoming months (2020/2021). Currently working on samples from Botswana that have been send to us. Zircons obtained from these rocks will be analysed for U-Pb isotopes for dating as well as Lu-Hf isotopes for implications on the crustal evolution during the Archaean.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Denice', 'last_name': 'Borsten', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Master student geology and geochemistry'}]}, {'title': 'Obtaining provenance of pre-Columbian ceramics in the Caribbean through portable laser ablation techniques', 'date': {'start': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}, 'end': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, 'description': 'BSc thesis project using Portable Laser Ablation, as part of the Bsc Earth sciences, completed with an 8 as the final grade.
